The paper focuses on predicting human performance in interaction tasks, specifically target selection from a vertical list or menu. This falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of deep neural nets suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the incorporation of additional UI attributes, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
